Reporter: &quot;Do you think Southampton deserve to go the Wembley?&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;Yeah, they won both games.&quot;

Klopp on Paul Lambert: &quot;I know him, a very nice man. He's a Dortmund legend. He came to watch training with us. We did licences together.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp: &quot;Wolves are a pretty direct team. They have target players. Counter-pressing.&quot;

Klopp: &quot;We had a few knocks after the game. We will have to make a few changes. Lallana got a cut, needed stitches.&quot;<br />
<br />
Klopp on Markovic: &quot;Why should I say now no chance for Lazar? He's still a young boy. He has struggled with injuries.&quot;
